OL,6,FHeavy rain and bursts of thunder are
OL,7,Fforecast to hit Wales and south-west
OL,8,FEngland on Saturday, and thunderstorms
OL,9,Fmay develop in the East and South East.
OL,11,FSunday will be fresher, brighter,
OL,12,Fdrier, and will mainly stay around the
OL,13,Flow 20Cs, which is the July average.
OL,15,FBy Monday, the weather will be
OL,16,Fchangeable but the week ahead will
OL,17,Flargely be dry.
OL,19,FMet Office meteorologist Tom Morgan
OL,20,Fsaid temperatures could rise again
OL,21,F"right at the end of July".
